1 A BILL for an Act to provide for a legislative management study relating to health care services
2 in local correctional facilities.
3 BE IT ENACTED BY THE LEGISLATIVE ASSEMBLY OF NORTH DAKOTA:
4 SECTION 1. LEGISLATIVE MANAGEMENT STUDY - HEALTH CARE SERVICES IN
5 LOCAL CORRECTIONAL FACILITIES.
6 1. During the 2025-26 interim, the legislative management shall consider studying health
7 care services in local correctional facilities. The study must include:
8 a. A review of current state and federal requirements of local correctional facilities
9 regarding health care services;
10 b. A review of health care services funding patterns for local correctional facilities;
11 c. A consideration of the challenges of local health care facilities and providers in
12 serving incarcerated individuals in local correctional facilities;
13 d. An analysis of models of best practices for health care services for incarcerated
14 individuals in local correctional facilities; and
15 e. A consideration of methods to expand local, state, and federal funding for health
16 care services in local correctional facilities.
17 2. The legislative management shall report its findings and recommendations together
18 with any legislation required to implement the recommendations, to the seventieth
19 legislative assembly.
